{"body": "Sure. I didn't think about it.\r\n\r\n@josevalim, anonymous controllers are used anywhere, aren't they? I see code which supports them, but I can imagine only something like this:\r\n\r\n``` ruby\r\nSimpleRailsApp::Application.routes.draw do\r\n  klass = Class.new(ApplicationController){\r\n    def text\r\n      render text: 'demo'\r\n    end\r\n  }\r\n  get 'url', to: klass.action(:text)\r\nend\r\n```\r\n\r\nHm. It's not very nice.\r\n\r\nI found and patched a defect in anonymous controllers layout lookup and doubt should I pull it or not.", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/4210746", "created_at": "2012-02-28T07:05:38Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/5201#issuecomment-4210746", "updated_at": "2012-02-28T07:05:38Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 5201, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/avakhov", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://2.gravatar.com/avatar/54e74983d81fa2fbe4c28e8392532f18?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2Fedb3b863d9333073200581afe223ec23.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/received_events", "gravatar_id": "54e74983d81fa2fbe4c28e8392532f18", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "avakhov", "type": "User", "id": 92554, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/avakhov/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "52381b66bd3543c15100e3f1"}, "id": 4210746, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/5201"}
